		"description": "<p>You have learned to channel the frenzy that burns within your blood to the purpose of magical destruction.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>While you are in a @UUID[Compendium.a5e-bloody-heretics.bloody-heretics.Item.eSbauOXs2C1ajtDf]{Blood Frenzy}, you may choose to cast a spell that deals damage or forces a saving throw than making a melee attack against them. &nbsp;The spell must target or center its area on the creature nearest to you. &nbsp;If the spell deals damage, it deals adds an additional 1d6 points of damage of the same type to one of its damage rolls. If you cast a spell in this way during a Blood Frenzy, you may then make a weapon attack against the same creature as a bonus action.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with your choice of the Sanctified Steel or Cutting Omen combat traditions. You learn one bonus maneuver from the chosen tradition.</li>\n</ul>",
